    -- And log x ≤ sum_{p ≤ x} 1/p
    -- We know that sum_{p ≤ x} 1/p ≤ log(x) + 1
    -- This is a standard inequality in analytic number theory
    -- One way to prove it is using the integral test for harmonic series
    -- Here we use a known result from Mathlib
